{
  "texts": [
    "• The assumptions made should be given (e.g., Normally distributed errors).",
    "• It should be clear whether the error bar is the standard deviation or the standard error of the mean.• It is OK to report 1-sigma error bars, but one should state it.",
    "The authors should preferably report a 2-sigma error bar than state that they have a 96% CI, if the hypothesis of Normality of errors is not verified.",
    "• For asymmetric distributions, the authors should be careful not to show in tables or figures symmetric error bars that would yield results that are out of range (e.g.",
    "negative error rates)."
  ]
}